  "pr_number": 566,
  "issue_number": 494,
  "issue_title": "feat(raycast): add trending and recent updates commands",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nRaycast currently focuses on search, category browsing, jobs, submissions, and contribution links. Dedicated Trending and Recent Updates commands would make the extension more useful for discovery and daily use.\n\n## Current state\n\n- Raycast category commands are thin wrappers around the registry command.\n- The MCP package has `get_recent_updates`, and the web API has registry changelog/diff artifacts.\n- There is no Raycast command for \u201cwhat changed\u201d or \u201cwhat is currently getting attention.\u201d\n\n## Desired behavior\n\n- Add a Recent Updates command backed by registry changelog/diff or a stable recent updates endpoint.\n- Add a Trending command once the public trending endpoint exists.\n- Keep actions consistent with existing entries: open, copy summary, copy asset, favorite, submit/suggest change.\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n- This can build on existing `RaycastEntry` parsing if endpoint payloads share entry summaries.\n- Avoid creating a separate visual language; reuse the current list/detail/action conventions.\n- Keep cached fallback behavior for failed endpoint calls.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- New commands are present in the Raycast manifest.\n- Recent updates and trending lists load from public HeyClaude surfaces.\n- Existing read-only safety tests remain true.\n- Tests cover parsers, filters, and cache behavior.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `npm test` from the Raycast extension directory\n- `npm run lint` from the Raycast extension directory\n- `npm run build` from the Raycast extension directory\n- Add or update focused unit tests for the touched API/helper surface.\n- Run the narrow relevant validation command for the changed package or route.\n- Run `git diff --check` before opening a PR.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-03T08:15:41.000Z",
